<SECOND>AM-BRF-McDonald's Shooting, 2nd Ld-Writethru, a0753,0169</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two McDonald's Employees Shot To Death In Robbery, Suspect Arrested</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS final graf to CORRECT victim's names; Reider sted Rider;
Hegarty sted Haggerty</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST CHESTER, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two employees of a McDonald's Restaurant
were fatally shot during a robbery Sunday and a suspect was arrested
hours later at a Wilmington, Del., bus station, officials said.
   Robert P. Hughes IV, 21, of Glen Mills, was arrested at about
8:40 a.m., said Wilmington police Sgt. Richard Andress. Hughes was
charged with resisting arrest, carrying a concealed deadly weapon
and was held as a fugitive, Andress said.
   In Pennsylvania, Hughes was charged with two counts of murder,
two counts of criminal homicide, robbery and weapons violations,
said James P. MacElree II, Chester County district attorney.
   Extradition proceedings probably will begin this week, Andress
said.
   Restaurant manager Jean Reider, 41, of Newark, Del., and Charles
Hegarty, 46, of West Chester, were killed in the holdup, which
occurred before the restaurant had opened, police said.
</TEXT>
