<FIRST>r a PM-GangViolence     01-09 0210</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Gang Violence,0215</SECOND>
<HEAD>Weekend Gang, Drug Violence Kills Three, Injures Five</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gang and drug-related violence left at least
three people dead and five wounded over the weekend, including a
20-year-old man gunned down as he rode with a teen-ager on a
bicycle, authorities said today.
   Danny Perez and a 16-year-old boy were taken to County-USC
Medical Center after a shooting in East Los Angeles on Friday
evening, sheriff's Deputy Chris Wahla said today.
   Perez was pronounced dead at the hospital. The 16-year-old's
condition was not released, said Wahla.
   Meanwhile, Irvin Smith, 36, was killed and another unidentified
man was injured when they were hit by a hail of gunfire late
Saturday, said Lt. Frank Valdez. He said the shooting was
narcotics-related.
   In Compton on Friday, 23-year-old David Berkley was shot and
killed in what was believed to be a gang-related attack, said police
Lt. Gary Anderson.
   Compton police were also investigating possible gang links to two
separate shootings, one of them a drive-by attack at 10:30 p.m.
Sunday in which two men and a woman were injured, said Anderson.
   The men were in critical condition and the woman was in good
condition at Martin Luther King Jr.-Drew Medical Center, Anderson
said. They were not identified.
</TEXT>
