<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--McDonald'sShooting     01-09 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--McDonald's Shooting,0164</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two McDonald's Employees Shot To Death In Robbery, Suspect Arrested</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST CHESTER, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Extradition proceedings for a man
accused of killing two McDonald's restaurant employees and then
arrested in Delaware will begin this week, police said.
   Robert P. Hughes IV, 21, of the suburban Philadelphia community
of Glen Mills, is charged with the two shooting deaths Sunday
morning, officials said.
   Restaurant manager Jean Reider, 41, of Newark, Del., and Charles
Hegarty, 46, of West Chester, were killed in the holdup, which
occurred before the restaurant had opened, police said.
   Hughes was arrested at the bus terminal in Wilmington, Del.,
several hours later, according to Wilmington police Sgt. Richard
Andress. He was charged with resisting arrest, carrying a concealed
deadly weapon and held as a fugitive, Andress said.
   In Pennsylvania, Hughes was charged with two counts of murder,
two counts of criminal homicide, robbery and weapons violations,
said James P. MacElree II, Chester County district attorney.
</TEXT>
