<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Italy-Fog     01-09 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Italy-Fog,0117</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fog Snarls Traffic in Road, Air</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILAN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thick fog that cut visibility to a few yards
disrupted road and air traffic in northern Italy for the third
consecutive day Monday.
   International airports in Milan, Venice, Turin and Bologna were
closed Monday and most flights were rerouted to Genoa or other
airports.
   Three people, including a 6-month-old child, were killed in a
road accident in the fog near Imola, south of Bologna, on Sunday
night, police said.
   In another accident, three students drowned Sunday night when
their car plunged off a road in the fog into a canal near the port
of Senigallia, a resort near Ancona, police said.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
