<FIRST>r i AM-Quake-Congressmen     01-09 0125</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Quake-Congressmen,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>U.S. Congressmen Visit Quake Victims in Yerevan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four U.S. congressmen on Monday handed out gifts to
children who were injured in the Armenian earthquake, the official
Soviet news agency Tass reported.
   The delegation, which visited the children in hospitals in the
Armenian capital of Yerevan, includes Reps. Tony Coelho, D-Calif.,
House majority whip; Robert K. Dornan, R-Calif.; David E. Bonior,
D-Mich.; and Robert G. Torricelli, D-N.J.
   The congressmen viewed earthquake damage on the four-day trip and
will report back to the House Task Force on Soviet Armenia.
   The group also met with the chairman of the Armenian Council of
Ministers, F.T. Sarkisian, who thanked them for U.S. participation
in the relief efforts follwoing the Dec. 7 earthquake, Tass said.
</TEXT>
