<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Japan-HongKong     01-09 0129</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Japan-Hong Kong,0132</SECOND>
<HEAD>Three Hong Kong Men Arrested in Slaying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police arrested three Hong Kong men in the slaying
of a 72-year-old Japanese factory owner who was stabbed during a
robbery attempt on his home.
   The three sneaked into the home of Masataro Kawaguchi, owner of a
leather and fur product manufacturing plant, on Saturday night and
stabbed Kawaguchi when he detected them, said a police official.
   Hearing screams, Kawaguchi's son rushed from a second-floor
bedroom and scared away the assailants, who fled in a car, the
official said.
   Japanese newspapers said the three arrived in Japan on Friday as
tourists.
   The official said police arrested two of the men on the street
four hours after the slaying and seized the third man on Sunday.
</TEXT>
