<HEAD>Pregnant Pathologist Found Beaten to Death in Hospital Lab</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 3 grafs to CORRECT victim's age to 33 sted 34, UPDATE
with authorities confirming she had been raped. Picks up 4th graf pvs,
`It was...'.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The savage beating death of a pregnant
33-year-old physician at Bellevue Hospital has triggered a major
police investigation and a review of security at the shaken
institution, officials said.
   ``This is a major case and at least 50 detectives are assigned to
it,'' Police Commissioner Benjamin Ward said after the body of Dr.
Kathryn Hinnant was found in a laboratory office Sunday morning by
her husband.
   Authorities today said that Ms. Hinnant had been raped and robbed
of $75 and a mink coat.
   ``It was a particularly brutal, outrageous murder,'' said Mayor
Edward I. Koch, who termed it a ``No. 1 case to be solved.''
   The city offered a $30,000 reward for information.
   Officials said security at the 1,200-bed municipal hospital would
be reviewed, but an initial check found nothing out of the ordinary
at the time of the murder.
   Her husband, Eric Johnson, 33, a piano salesman, said she was
five months pregnant. Police have said he is not a suspect.
   Officials said he was not unduly worried at first when his wife
didn't return from work Saturday evening. But when she did not call
or come home overnight, Johnson went to the hospital Sunday morning.
He and a hospital administrator found Ms. Hinnant's body in a small,
fourth-floor office.
   Hinnant, a native of Columbia, S.C., was a 1982 graduate of the
Medical University of South Carolina and had worked in Washington
before coming to Bellevue in 1987, police said.
</TEXT>
