<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Italy-Prostitution     01-09 0085</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Italy-Prostitution ,0087</SECOND>
<HEAD>Hotel Doorman Convicted of Procuring Prostitutes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former night doorman at Rome's Cavalieri Hilton
Hotel was convicted Monday of procuring prostitutes for guests.
   The hotel manager and two former clerks were acquitted of the
same charges.
   The former doorman, Roberto Gagliardi, received a suspended
sentence of one year and 10 months in prison.
   The hotel employees were arrested in May after police broke up a
prostitution ring at the luxury hotel, located on a hilltop
overlooking the capital.
</TEXT>
