<FIRST>r i AM-Greenpeace     01-09 0121</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Greenpeace,0125</SECOND>
<HEAD>Greenpeace Activists Protest at French Embassy in Bonn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 20 Greenpeace activists dressed
as penguins demonstrated in front of the French Embassy on Monday to
protest the building of a landing strip at a French research station
in the Antarctic.
   The environmentalists charged that the project, at the Dumont d'
Urville station, is damaging the ecology of the region and threatens
the habitat of thousands of sea birds and penguins.
   Other Greenpeace activists have staged protests at the site and
have attempted to block construction efforts.
   A Greenpeace statement released in West Germany said protesters
had been roughed up by French officials at the site.
   The group is demanding an immediate construction halt.
</TEXT>
