<SECOND>PM-Wall Street Noon,0322</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market edged upward today, running into
some resistance at its highest levels in nearly 15 months.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, which rose 25.72 points
last week, gained another 1.07 to 2,195.36 by noontime today on Wall
Street.
   Gainers outnumbered losers by about 7 to 6 in nationwide trading
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 681 up, 589 down and
562 unchanged.
   The market has benefited in recent sessions from buying by money
managers at investing institutions seeking to put some of their
large cash reserves to work at the start of a new year.
   But analysts said traders were worried that the rally had
encountered some large obstacles.
   Each time the Dow Jones industrial average reached the 2,000
level last week, selling pressure seemed to intensify.
