<FIRST>r f AM-PublisherNamed     01-09 0217</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Publisher Named,0224</SECOND>
<HEAD>Newspaper Editor Appointed Publisher of Delaware Business Review</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DOVER, Del. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Delaware State News Editor Frank Fantini has
been appointed publisher of the Delaware Business Review, but will
continue to write a column for the State News opinion pages.
   Fantini, 42, has been general manager of Delaware's only business
journal since November 1987, splitting his time between the
newspaper in the state capital and the business publication in
Wilmington.
   ``This is a special opportunity,'' Fantini said of the publishing
job.
   ``My column will allow me to continue to share in a great
enthusiasm _ the growth and maturation of Dover into a true city.''
   Fantini began at the State News as a reporter in 1974 after three
years as a reporter and news editor of the Cecil Whig in Elkton, Md.
   He covered local government and later state government and
politics for the State News, moving to news editor in 1977, managing
editor in 1981, executive editor in 1982 and editor in 1988.
   He will be in charge of the 10,600-circulation Delaware Business
Review, which, like the State News, is owned by Independent
Newspapers Inc., headquartered in Dover. The corporation also owns
The Whale and Sussex Post in Delaware, the Cambridge (Md.) Banner
and other non-daily newspapers in Maryland, Florida and Arizona.
</TEXT>
