<FIRST>r f AM-Buick-Layoffs     01-09 0339</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Buick-Layoffs,0354</SECOND>
<HEAD>GM Laying Off 100 at Reatta Factory</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By FREDERICK STANDISH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 100 General Motors Corp. Buick Division
workers will be laid off as the automaker cuts production of its
Reatta luxury two-seat car, a company spokesman said Monday.
   Larry Gustin said production levels at the Reatta Craft Center in
Lansing would be cut Feb. 13 from 56 to 42 cars daily.
   Some of the layoffs would come as early as Jan. 20 when the plant
is shut down for installation of a new paint process and some new
tooling for a Reatta convertible, Gustin said.
   There are about 780 employees currently at the plant, which
produces only the Reatta.
   Overly optimistic sales forecasts prompted the cutback, Gustin
said.
   ``The manufacturing operation had been set up in a more
optimistic mode than our forecasts,'' Gustin said, in part because
of yet-to-be seen convertible sales.
   Originally, the Reatta convertible was to be introduced late last
fall, but Gustin said company officials decided more development
time was needed and put off introduction of the soft top until fall
1989.
   Analyst Kathleen Heaney of Nikko Securities Co. International
Inc. of New York, said GM had ambitious production schedules during
the last three months of 1988. The monthly sales rates of Reatta
rose during the second half of last year compared with the first
half, to 480 cars a month from 272.
   Most of that increase came in the last quarter.
   Between Reatta's introduction Jan. 15, 1988, and the end of last
year, Buick dealers sold 4,514 of the cars.
   ``We have forecast 7,000 to 8,000 in sales for the '89 model
year,'' Gustin said.
   ``It's still a momentum-building car looking for a new market
niche,'' he said. ``I think the manufacturing side felt that we
would do better than that.''
   The front-wheel-drive Reatta, which retails for $26,700, has as
its only options a 16-way adjustable driver's seat and a power
sunroof. Standard equipment includes a keyless entry system,
anti-lock brakes, air-conditioning and leather seats.
</TEXT>
